<p>I want to know the porper way to create the singleton class.Currently I am doing in the following way. In the .h file I am declaring the instance of the class in the following way.</p>  <pre><code>@interface GlobalMethods : NSObject { } + (GlobalMethods *)sharedInstance; </code></pre>  <p>And in the .m file I did the code in the following way.</p>  <pre><code>@implementation GlobalMethods - (id)init { self = [super init]; if (self) {     //Custom Intialization }  return self; }  + (GlobalMethods *)sharedInstance {      static GlobalMethods *sharedInstance = nil;      @synchronized(self)      {          if (sharedInstance == NULL)          {               sharedInstance = [[GlobalMethods alloc] init];          }       return sharedInstance;  } </code></pre>  <p>}</p>